33 SUMMARY
3344 This amendment does the following.
35 1. It makes changes to the required qualifications for an at-large member of the Finance
36 Authority of Maine appointed by the Governor.
37 2. It makes changes to the qualification requirements for commissioners of the Maine
38 State Housing Authority appointed by the Governor.
39 3. It changes certain references to the Governor's Energy Office in the Maine Revised
40 Statutes, Title 35-A to the Department of Energy Resources.
Page 16 - 132LR1752(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 845, L.D. 1270
1 4. It amends the Maine Wind Energy Act to direct the Department of Energy Resources
2 to issue the first request for proposals and select resources for contracts. The Public
3 Utilities Commission is responsible for approving such contracts.
4 5. It requires the Department of Energy Resources, when conducting planning,
5 developing and implementing policies and establishing programs, to address energy
6 burdens.
7 6. It prohibits the Commissioner of Energy Resources from, for a period of 12 months
8 after the completion of the commissioner's service, participating on behalf of a bidder in
9 the submission of a proposal in response to a competitive solicitation conducted by the
10 Department of Energy Resources.
11 7. It requires the Department of Energy Resources, when preparing the comprehensive
12 state energy plan, to seek input regarding issues faced by socially vulnerable counties and
13 communities.
14 8. It requires the Department of Energy Resources, to the extent practicable while
15 protecting the energy security of the State, to submit the state energy security plan to the
16 joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over energy matters.
17 9. It requires the Department of Energy Resources to ensure that the State's energy
18 goals, policies and plans align with and support the achievement of greenhouse gas
19 emissions obligations and climate goals.
20 10. It removes the specific date by which the Department of Energy Resources must
21 develop the Distributed Solar and Energy Storage Program.
22 11. It makes the failure to file or the inclusion of false or misleading information in
23 reports related to petroleum product inventories and deliveries a civil violation and removes
24 the provisions of the bill making certain violations of reporting requirements criminal
25 offenses.
26 12. It makes changes to the Department of Energy Resources' authority to initiate and
27 conduct procurements for energy, associated environmental attributes or other services
28 from renewable and clean resources, including establishing objectives and requirements for
29 the department's conduct of competitive solicitations, requiring the department to consult
30 with the Office of the Public Advocate in developing requests for proposals and
31 establishing requirements for the review of the request for proposals and approval of
32 contracts by the Public Utilities Commission. It requires that, if the department selects a
33 project for a contract for energy, associated environmental attributes or other services from
34 renewable and clean resources involving the construction of the project, contractors and
35 subcontractors involved in the project's construction must adhere to certain community and
36 workforce enhancement standards and apprenticeship standards. The amendment provides
37 for the confidential treatment of proposals submitted in response to a solicitation conducted
38 by the department and materials created or submitted during related contract negotiations.
39 The amendment also requires the department to conduct the first procurement by January
40 15, 2026.
41 13. It removes the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over
42 energy, utilities and technology matters from the review to be conducted by staff from the
43 Office of Policy and Legal Analysis and the Office of the Revisor of Statutes of those parts
44 of the Maine Revised Statutes governing the administration and activities of the Governor's
Page 17 - 132LR1752(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 845, L.D. 1270
415 Energy Office to correct any errors and inconsistencies in the law that result from this
426 legislation.
