COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 845, L.D. 1270
1 B. Evaluate energy data, including, but not limited to, data on energy supply, demand
2 and costs in this State with consideration of all available energy sources;
3 C. Detail the State's progress toward meeting its energy goals for new renewable
4 energy generation and energy storage, including distributed energy resources;
5 D. Evaluate the State's progress in meeting the oil dependence reduction targets in
6 section 10309;
7 E. Identify resource and transmission and distribution capacity and infrastructure
8 needs to facilitate the development and integration of new renewable energy generation
9 within the State and support the State's renewable resource portfolio requirements
10 specified in section 3210 in close coordination with the independent system operator
11 of the New England bulk power system or a successor organization, the Public Utilities
12 Commission's integrated grid planning under section 3147 and transmission and
13 distribution utilities;
14 F. Address the association between energy planning and meeting the greenhouse gas
15 emissions reduction goals in the state climate action plan pursuant to Title 38, section
16 577;
17 G. Include a cost and resource estimate for technology development to meet the goals
18 and objectives of the state energy plan;
19 H. Include energy supply and demand forecasts that must be considered in other
20 planning efforts including updates to the state climate action plan under Title 38,
21 section 577 and the Efficiency Maine Trust's triennial plan under section 10104,
22 subsection 4; and
23 I. Identify approximate total project award targets for the next 3 competitive
24 solicitations to be conducted by the department pursuant to section 10313.
25 The joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over energy matters
26 may report out legislation by April 1st of each odd-numbered year relating to the content
27 of the state energy plan. The joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction
28 over natural resources matters may make recommendations regarding that legislation to the
29 joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over energy matters;
30 2. Recommendations. Make recommendations, if needed, for additional legislative
31 and administrative actions to ensure that the State can meet the goals and objectives of the
32 state energy plan under subsection 1. The department shall develop, recommend and, as
33 appropriate, take action to implement integrated or comprehensive strategies, including at
34 regional and federal levels, to carry out the goals and objectives of the state energy plan, to
35 secure the State's interest in energy resources and the supply and cost-effective use of those
36 resources and lower the total cost of energy to consumers in this State;
37 3. Annual report. By January 15th of each year, prepare and submit to the joint
38 standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over energy matters a report that
39 describes the activities of the department during the previous calendar year in carrying out
40 its duties under this section and describes the State's progress in implementation of the state
41 energy plan prepared pursuant to subsection 1, funding received from private sources
42 pursuant to section 10308, subsection 3 and the department's annual accounting pursuant
43 to section 10308, subsection 2. After receipt and review of the annual report, the joint
44 standing committee may report out legislation relating to energy policy;
